<div class="row">
  <div class="columns text-center">
    <h1>Checkout out interesting data!</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="small-12 large-8 columns">
    <div id="container2" style="width:100%; height:400px;"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
    <div class="green-container">
      <h4>Armenia's population and energy use dips in 1990</h4>
      <p>What happened?<br>Armenia declares independence from the Soviet Union.
        <br>But what really caused the energy dip and population decrease?
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="small-12 large-8 columns">
      <div id="container" style="width:100%; height:400px;"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
      <div class="green-container">
        <h4>Iceland and their huge energy consumption</h4>
        <p>Iceland's energy use grew exponentially after 1998
          because of they became a large scale manufacturing country,
          especially aluminum.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="small-12 large-7 columns">
      <div id="world_pie" style="width:100%; height:300px;"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="small-12 large-5 columns">
      <div class="green-container">
        <h4>Endangered Animals around the World</h4>
        <p>
          Are you surprised about the amount of envulnerable animals as I am?
          There are almost 50k animals that are near extinction!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "data/two_datasets" %>

<script>
$(function () {
  $('#container').highcharts({
    chart: { type: 'spline' },
    title: {
      text: '<%= @energy["title"] %>'
    },
    xAxis: {
      type: 'datetime',
      dateTimeLabelFormats: { year: '%Y' },
      title: { text: 'Year' }
    },
    yAxis: {
      title: { text: '<%= @energy["title"] %>' }
    },
    tooltip: {
      headerFormat: '<b>{series.name}</b><br>',
      pointFormat: '{point.x:%Y}: {point.y:.1f}'
    },
    plotOptions: {
      spline: {
        marker: {
          enabled: true
        }
      }
    },
    series: [<% @energy["data"].each do |data| %>
      {
        name: '<%= data["country"] %>',
        data: <%= data["data"] %>
      },
      <% end %>
    ]
  });
});
</script>
